WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:51.134
ALL FIGURES,
INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,

00:51.217 --> 00:52.469
ORGANIZATIONS,
AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS

00:52.552 --> 00:53.887
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

00:53.970 --> 00:54.971
IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES.

00:56.848 --> 00:58.808
<i>What in the world</i>
<i>do you think you've been up to?</i>

00:58.892 --> 01:01.311
Why keep doing something unnecessary?

01:01.895 --> 01:04.564
An attorney proved her client's innocence.

01:04.647 --> 01:05.607
What's the problem?

01:08.985 --> 01:11.237
All the animals
that escaped the lab because of you

01:11.321 --> 01:13.573
were their research subjects.

01:13.656 --> 01:16.326
They even claimed damages against us.

01:17.035 --> 01:18.953
I did it to catch the murderer.

01:19.037 --> 01:20.038
You're not a prosecutor.

01:22.665 --> 01:23.750
What's with you lately?

01:24.667 --> 01:27.003
First, you hand over
evidence against us to the police

01:27.086 --> 01:29.088
and then, you sue an artist
of our partnered client.

01:29.672 --> 01:31.674
Why do you keep blowing things
out of proportion?

01:31.758 --> 01:35.303
I couldn't turn a blind eye to those
who obviously committed crimes.

01:38.807 --> 01:40.892
There's a limit to my patience
as a partner attorney.

01:40.975 --> 01:43.019
Am I even a partner attorney to you?

01:44.020 --> 01:44.854
What?

01:44.938 --> 01:47.732
If you took me for a partner attorney,

01:47.816 --> 01:52.070
you'd hear my side of the story first
instead of accusing me.

01:52.153 --> 01:55.990
Your side of the story? I can already tell
you're messing things up everywhere.

01:57.367 --> 01:59.244
I'm a managing partner of Taebaek.

01:59.327 --> 02:02.705
It's my job to discipline attorneys
who can't get their act together.

02:04.332 --> 02:05.333
Exactly.

02:06.459 --> 02:08.837
You're only doing your job,

02:09.379 --> 02:12.507
so why do I sense personal feelings?

02:14.717 --> 02:15.552
When did I do that?

02:18.138 --> 02:19.347
This time again,

02:19.430 --> 02:23.101
you'll be given the kind of punishment
you deserve. End of discussion.

02:25.645 --> 02:26.980
No.

02:27.063 --> 02:27.981
I quit.

02:29.983 --> 02:32.443
I'll compensate you
for the damages in a week.

02:33.027 --> 02:34.696
Are you saying you'll leave Taebaek?

02:35.405 --> 02:36.239
Who says you can?

02:36.322 --> 02:37.574
Me.

02:40.326 --> 02:43.538
You're the one who wanted to join Taebaek.

02:43.621 --> 02:44.789
That's right.

02:44.873 --> 02:47.125
But without the Chairman,

02:47.750 --> 02:49.460
Taebaek isn't Taebaek anymore.

02:58.469 --> 03:00.346
I give her an inch,
and she tries to take a mile.

03:05.059 --> 03:07.937
TAEBAEK LAW FIRM

03:22.243 --> 03:24.996
PARTNER LAWYER HAN NA-HYUN

04:00.406 --> 04:01.616
Welcome.

04:02.492 --> 04:04.994
I'm sorry for entering without permission.

04:06.120 --> 04:08.081
Don't be. I know you've come a long way.

04:08.790 --> 04:09.707
A long way?

04:09.791 --> 04:13.878
No one can see you,
and you don't remember a thing.

04:13.962 --> 04:16.881
It must've been so lonely to be invisible.

04:17.465 --> 04:18.800
I'm not quite following--

04:18.883 --> 04:20.385
I understand how flustered you are.

04:20.885 --> 04:22.470
Let me explain it one after another.

04:23.179 --> 04:24.639
-Have a seat.
-What…

04:24.722 --> 04:25.723
I-rang, what's up?

04:25.807 --> 04:27.684
-Hi, Bong-su.
-Hi.

04:28.226 --> 04:30.353
-Hello.
-Hello.

04:33.064 --> 04:34.065
What the?

04:34.816 --> 04:36.276
You can see him too?

04:36.901 --> 04:38.069
Yes.

04:40.738 --> 04:42.198
Liar.

04:42.282 --> 04:43.449
I know you can't.

04:44.075 --> 04:45.451
-Ouch! What…
-Goodness.

04:52.250 --> 04:54.168
-W-Who are you?
-Why did you hit me?

04:54.252 --> 04:55.586
I'm the new security here!

04:56.838 --> 04:57.964
I'm sorry!

04:58.047 --> 05:00.341
A-Are you okay? Sorry about this.

05:01.342 --> 05:03.720
What are you doing? Carrying fire
in one hand and water in the other?

05:03.803 --> 05:06.889
I-I mistook you for a ghost.
I'm truly sorry.

05:06.973 --> 05:09.475
Does my face look like a ghost?

05:09.559 --> 05:11.853
What in the world… I've had enough!

05:11.936 --> 05:12.895
Wait…

05:17.025 --> 05:19.694
I-rang, why did you have to do that?

05:25.658 --> 05:26.701
I don't see any.

05:27.285 --> 05:28.828
S-See what?

05:28.911 --> 05:30.163
I don't hear any, Bong-su.

05:33.666 --> 05:34.751
I'm finally free from them!

05:35.960 --> 05:36.961
Yes!

05:37.045 --> 05:38.421
Hooray!

05:39.380 --> 05:41.758
Hooray for I-rang's independence!

05:41.841 --> 05:44.969
Hooray!

05:48.097 --> 05:49.182
Ghosts aren't coming?

05:49.265 --> 05:51.976
He says it's been more than two weeks now.

05:52.060 --> 05:54.062
Maybe it was a temporary thing.

05:55.313 --> 05:56.647
You must be happy, Mother.

05:57.273 --> 05:59.859
You didn't show it,
but you were quite concerned.

06:00.777 --> 06:01.611
Right.

06:02.236 --> 06:04.072
I sure am glad to hear the news.

06:04.614 --> 06:05.448
What did I-rang say?

06:05.531 --> 06:07.742
He's cleaning
for his future living clients.

06:07.825 --> 06:09.494
He's so excited.

06:33.059 --> 06:35.228
What are you doing?
Do you want to play hide-and-seek?

06:36.938 --> 06:38.689
Oh, my. That must be painful.

06:46.614 --> 06:48.866
Come on, mister.

06:50.243 --> 06:51.577
That's so distracting.

06:51.661 --> 06:55.206
Will you stop already?

07:06.926 --> 07:07.885
What the heck!

07:08.511 --> 07:09.929
This can't be.

07:10.513 --> 07:11.764
What is going on?

07:34.662 --> 07:36.164
No.

07:36.247 --> 07:39.584
There's no way I'm missing the ghosts.

07:40.251 --> 07:41.169
No.

07:41.752 --> 07:43.838
Hey, Shin I-rang.

07:44.422 --> 07:45.423
Pull yourself together.

07:46.132 --> 07:47.633
You've finally been set free.

07:57.393 --> 08:00.396
After how you left that day,

08:00.980 --> 08:02.690
I felt a little sorry.

08:03.733 --> 08:06.819
Attorneys don't always win their cases.

08:07.403 --> 08:09.238
And mistakes are bound to be made.

08:09.780 --> 08:11.407
I was too harsh on you.

08:11.491 --> 08:13.159
Please don't bother.

08:14.702 --> 08:17.497
I compensated the lab for the damages.

08:17.580 --> 08:18.456
You've heard, right?

08:18.539 --> 08:23.252
You didn't have to.
I only said that to tell you off.

08:32.970 --> 08:33.804
Here.

08:36.974 --> 08:37.850
What is this?

08:38.726 --> 08:39.852
Traineeship overseas.

08:40.728 --> 08:41.771
It may be called training,

08:41.854 --> 08:43.898
but you can take a break to travel
and clear your head.

08:44.857 --> 08:46.025
In New York.

08:46.984 --> 08:49.445
Afterwards, return to Taebaek.

08:50.738 --> 08:51.948
No, thank you.

08:54.492 --> 08:56.661
Is it because I hurt your pride
the other day?

08:58.496 --> 09:00.706
That's why I came all the way here.

09:01.874 --> 09:03.417
Let it go now.

09:04.001 --> 09:06.254
-I'm not going back.
-Okay, fine.

09:07.213 --> 09:09.382
It wouldn't be you
if you didn't refuse three times.

09:09.465 --> 09:11.175
I'll ask you three more times.

09:11.717 --> 09:13.553
-Come back.
-I won't.

09:14.887 --> 09:16.556
-Come back.
-I won't.

09:17.974 --> 09:20.893
-Come back.
-No, no, no, I won't!

09:20.977 --> 09:22.395
I'm not going back.

09:24.605 --> 09:25.690
Okay?

09:29.443 --> 09:31.279
Take this with you while you're at it.

09:53.801 --> 09:56.721
Let's see how long you can last.

10:03.144 --> 10:04.312
Hello, Mr. Choi.

10:05.354 --> 10:07.565
Stop Han Na-hyun
from joining any law firm.

10:09.066 --> 10:11.319
Call all the law firms out there.

10:15.698 --> 10:17.533
If you have nowhere else to go,

10:18.242 --> 10:19.243
you'll come back to me.

10:21.996 --> 10:23.456
KIM AND JEONG LAW FIRM,
HWASEOL LAW FIRM,

10:23.539 --> 10:24.999
BHN LAW FIRM,
YSP LAW FIRM, SP LAW FIRM

10:25.666 --> 10:27.251
You used to work at Taebaek.

10:27.335 --> 10:30.880
Taebaek certainly is
one of the top performing law firms.

10:30.963 --> 10:33.799
However, I believe my convictions
align with your founding philosophy

10:33.883 --> 10:37.928
of prioritizing basic ethics and values
and upholding social responsibility

10:38.012 --> 10:41.474
rather than performance and profit,
which is why I've decided to apply.

10:54.070 --> 10:56.113
…WE ARE INADEQUATE
TO EMBODY YOUR NOBLE ASPIRATIONS

10:57.823 --> 10:58.991
They turned me down?

11:00.076 --> 11:02.161
…WE ARE UNABLE TO MOVE
FORWARD WITH YOU THIS TIME

11:03.621 --> 11:04.497
What?

11:07.500 --> 11:09.627
…YOUR VISION DOES NOT ALIGN
WITH OUR CURRENT DIRECTION

11:09.710 --> 11:10.753
Again?

11:11.754 --> 11:14.048
Attorney Han Na-hyun, please come in.

11:15.925 --> 11:17.927
LATERAL HIRING
ATTORNEY INTERVIEWS

11:18.010 --> 11:20.012
INTERVIEW ROOM

11:25.267 --> 11:26.435
Please have a seat.

11:29.271 --> 11:30.439
Care to ask a question?

11:44.161 --> 11:47.164
I don't have any questions for Mr. Shin.

11:58.342 --> 11:59.343
What do you think you're doing?

11:59.427 --> 12:01.137
JOB APPLICATION
NAME: HAN NA-HYUN

12:03.514 --> 12:04.807
That's my question to ask.

12:09.728 --> 12:10.855
What…

12:11.439 --> 12:12.481
I'm turning you down.

12:13.357 --> 12:17.319
I'm turning you down
because you're way below my level.

12:22.408 --> 12:23.659
-I-rang.
-Yes?

12:23.742 --> 12:25.536
Here's your utility bill.

12:25.619 --> 12:27.037
Oh, thanks.

12:27.121 --> 12:28.747
It's a lot.

12:29.957 --> 12:32.084
Are you going somewhere fancy, Bong-su?

12:34.879 --> 12:36.297
I'm starting a new gig today.

12:36.380 --> 12:37.548
Really?

12:37.631 --> 12:38.883
What's your role this time?

12:38.966 --> 12:41.343
I told you about it before.

12:41.427 --> 12:42.511
It's a paralegal.

12:44.221 --> 12:46.682
Do you have many lines this time?

12:48.309 --> 12:51.020
Goodness, how can you be this positive?

12:51.645 --> 12:54.690
Aren't you worried at all?
Not even a rat walks into this office.

12:55.649 --> 12:56.775
I am.

12:56.859 --> 12:59.111
That's why I cleaned the whole place.

12:59.195 --> 13:00.654
What's the use of cleaning?

13:00.738 --> 13:03.199
It's in a remote area,
and it was a shaman's house for decades.

13:03.282 --> 13:05.201
How will you possibly have
clients come here?

13:05.284 --> 13:07.119
Not unless you advertise yourself.

13:07.786 --> 13:08.704
Advertise?

13:09.330 --> 13:12.416
Doesn't it cost a lot of money?

13:12.500 --> 13:14.043
What are your business cards for?

13:14.126 --> 13:16.670
There are clients
everywhere at the courthouse.

13:18.672 --> 13:23.344
It'd be really worthwhile
to visit those going through a hard time.

13:26.305 --> 13:27.139
You think?

13:27.890 --> 13:29.683
It's my line in the show.

13:30.935 --> 13:34.855
It might actually work for you
because you have an agreeable face.

13:34.939 --> 13:36.440
Good luck! See you.

13:41.529 --> 13:44.114
Well, he has a point.

13:50.871 --> 13:52.081
Advertise…

13:52.831 --> 13:54.041
INVOICE FOR DAMAGES

13:55.000 --> 13:57.002
TOTAL: 521,500,000 WON

13:57.878 --> 14:02.174
SILVERWELL LABORATORY
-521,500,000 WON

14:02.258 --> 14:06.303
MAY MAINTENANCE FEE
-171,180 WON

14:06.387 --> 14:10.975
JUNE MAINTENANCE FEE
-250,380 WON

14:17.231 --> 14:19.066
CURRENT BALANCE: 4,305,110 WON

14:21.235 --> 14:22.486
THIS IS GOOD DESIGN

14:22.570 --> 14:24.280
YOUR BUSINESS CARDS
HAVE BEEN DELIVERED

14:39.003 --> 14:41.380
ATTORNEY HAN NA-HYUN

14:42.006 --> 14:45.593
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

14:51.098 --> 14:53.058
Worthwhile, my butt.

15:07.823 --> 15:08.949
It must be hard on you.

15:09.950 --> 15:12.244
But you should stay strong
at a time like this.

15:12.328 --> 15:14.121
I'm here to help you--

15:14.204 --> 15:15.205
Not again.

15:15.998 --> 15:16.832
Excuse me?

15:16.916 --> 15:20.252
You're all talk
when you won't even take responsibility.

15:20.878 --> 15:24.006
"We need more materials.
Bring me crucial evidence."

15:24.089 --> 15:27.593
You shameless people make excuses
only to raise the legal fees.

15:27.676 --> 15:29.595
-No, I--
-Now,

15:29.678 --> 15:32.973
I hate you people
more than that jerk who cheated on me.

15:33.057 --> 15:35.225
I even shudder in my sleep
at the thought of lawyers!

15:40.522 --> 15:44.193
Why's she taking it out on me?
I didn't do anything.

15:49.782 --> 15:51.200
Nothing's easy.

15:59.583 --> 16:00.501
<i>Dad!</i>

16:01.627 --> 16:02.503
Hi.

16:09.969 --> 16:13.430
Don't waste your energy
on meaningless thoughts, I-rang.

16:17.768 --> 16:19.103
Mr. Bae?

16:19.186 --> 16:20.854
I-rang? Long time no see.

16:21.480 --> 16:22.773
Did you have a trial?

16:23.565 --> 16:24.441
You seem busy.

16:25.484 --> 16:27.695
I'm so tired. I have way too much work.

16:28.362 --> 16:29.279
I'm dying to rest.

16:30.864 --> 16:31.699
What's that?

16:31.782 --> 16:33.242
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

16:35.411 --> 16:37.913
I have no work,
so I'm out to advertise myself.

16:39.248 --> 16:42.459
Don't feel embarrassed.
That's how it is for solo attorneys.

16:44.336 --> 16:45.295
Want a case?

16:45.379 --> 16:46.380
What?

16:46.463 --> 16:49.091
I'm supposed to take it on,
but I already have my hands full.

16:49.758 --> 16:51.510
What is it about?

16:51.593 --> 16:53.012
I'm a little busy right now.

16:53.095 --> 16:55.097
Hear it from the client in person.

16:55.681 --> 16:56.682
I'll tell them about you.

16:56.765 --> 16:58.559
SEONGMYEONG CONSTRUCTION
YOON HYEON-SEOK

17:00.102 --> 17:03.313
You're the best. Thanks.

17:03.397 --> 17:05.232
Don't mention it.
I can do this much for you.

17:06.108 --> 17:07.776
I better get going. Bye.

17:07.860 --> 17:10.362
Okay. I'll repay you for this!

17:10.446 --> 17:12.072
Treat me to a drink some time.

17:12.656 --> 17:14.742
Hello. If you need an attorney…

17:17.703 --> 17:18.829
Please give me a call.

17:32.843 --> 17:35.971
MY FAMILY WON'T RETURN,
BUT JUSTICE MUST PREVAIL

17:38.223 --> 17:39.308
You're doing well.

17:39.850 --> 17:40.809
Are you sure?

17:40.893 --> 17:42.102
Make sure you eat well.

17:42.728 --> 17:43.729
I'll wait for your call.

17:45.272 --> 17:46.732
Thank you.

17:46.815 --> 17:47.941
Cheer up.

17:48.609 --> 17:49.568
Thank you.

17:56.366 --> 17:57.785
Attorney Han Na-hyun?

17:58.619 --> 18:01.413
No, you got the wrong person.

18:01.497 --> 18:03.082
I know it's you.

18:03.165 --> 18:07.044
Fair skin and a small face.
It is you, Attorney Han Na-hyun.

18:07.127 --> 18:08.545
No, I'm not.

18:09.630 --> 18:11.715
What? Yes, you are.

18:28.565 --> 18:30.359
Why is he following me?

18:30.901 --> 18:32.611
Attorney Han, why are you here?

18:32.694 --> 18:35.697
Why are you wearing sunglasses?
What's with those business cards?

18:37.533 --> 18:39.243
Did you get fired?

18:39.910 --> 18:41.120
It's not your business.

18:41.203 --> 18:43.831
Come on. Don't be so cold.

18:43.914 --> 18:46.917
We had such amazing teamwork
when we caught Gu Hyo-jung.

18:47.000 --> 18:49.086
Don't even mention his name.
It pisses me off.

18:53.173 --> 18:56.760
-This is so embarrassing.
-Attorney Han, are you okay? Are you hurt?

18:57.344 --> 18:58.804
Can't you just pretend not to know me?

18:58.887 --> 19:01.557
How can I possibly turn a blind eye
when you just tripped over?

19:04.059 --> 19:07.187
Anyway, did you really get fired?

19:07.271 --> 19:10.524
Both Su-jeong and Mr. Kim Tae-jun
were found not guilty.

19:10.607 --> 19:12.192
Wasn't that a good thing for Taebaek?

19:17.489 --> 19:19.158
This is all because of you.

19:19.241 --> 19:20.701
Because of you, my cases were a mess.

19:20.784 --> 19:22.786
Because of you,
a win didn't feel like a win,

19:22.870 --> 19:26.540
and I even ended up resigning, but now,
I'm going nuts with so much to pay for.

19:26.623 --> 19:28.792
So don't talk to me ever again, got it?

19:29.751 --> 19:32.880
If you follow me again,
I'll call the police.

19:36.049 --> 19:37.342
Wait.

19:37.426 --> 19:40.053
You can call the police
or even sue me, so hold on.

19:41.138 --> 19:43.307
Sit here for a sec.

19:44.141 --> 19:45.058
Let go.

19:51.815 --> 19:53.233
Let me. Geez.

19:54.234 --> 19:56.111
It snapped off completely.

19:56.904 --> 19:59.448
There's a skilled cobbler's shop nearby.

19:59.531 --> 20:00.532
I'll get it repaired soon.

20:01.200 --> 20:02.201
No, just give it to me.

20:02.284 --> 20:03.702
You can't walk in this.

20:03.785 --> 20:05.829
It'll take only ten minutes.
Wait here a little.

20:05.913 --> 20:06.830
Okay?

20:13.045 --> 20:14.838
What are they doing?

20:37.444 --> 20:38.445
Excuse me.

20:39.238 --> 20:40.072
Hello.

20:40.155 --> 20:41.740
Who are you?

20:41.823 --> 20:46.203
Didn't you talk to a woman
in front of the courthouse just now?

20:46.286 --> 20:48.080
A tall woman with sunglasses on.

20:48.705 --> 20:50.165
Oh, yes. I did.

20:51.917 --> 20:55.170
Your conversation ended in the middle
because of me.

20:56.338 --> 20:58.840
If you're looking to hire an attorney,

20:58.924 --> 21:03.220
you should really give that woman
a chance with your case.

21:03.303 --> 21:06.306
She's such a competent attorney, you see.

21:07.683 --> 21:09.476
I didn't know she was an attorney.

21:10.811 --> 21:11.645
Excuse me?

21:11.728 --> 21:14.856
She said she had done
a solo protest at the same spot

21:14.940 --> 21:17.442
about a wrongful car accident
during her second year in high school.

21:18.110 --> 21:20.570
She also said I needed
to be in good shape to keep fighting,

21:22.447 --> 21:24.533
and so I should eat well.

21:25.909 --> 21:29.371
I've never heard such a thing
from a complete stranger before.

21:30.038 --> 21:31.707
It was so warm.

22:03.071 --> 22:06.033
Her 2nd year in high school
was 13 years ago.

22:06.992 --> 22:08.577
That's 2012.

22:10.620 --> 22:12.581
YEAR 2012,
CAR ACCIDENT, SOLO PROTEST

22:16.543 --> 22:19.254
DUI FATALITY CASE'S VICTIM
CONTINUES A SOLO PROTEST

22:19.338 --> 22:21.715
CAN A LIFE BE REPLACED AT
THE COST OF TWO YEARS IN PRISON?

22:24.134 --> 22:24.968
VICTIM'S YOUNGER SISTER…

22:25.052 --> 22:26.053
IRRESPONSIBLE DRUNK DRIVING,

22:26.136 --> 22:27.846
"IS THE LAW
REALLY ON THE VICTIM'S SIDE?"

22:46.281 --> 22:49.076
I get it now.

22:49.618 --> 22:53.622
I get that you love money,
but you shouldn't make use of others.

22:54.289 --> 22:57.084
Those people are already having it hard…

23:00.337 --> 23:02.506
even if not for the likes of you.

23:04.216 --> 23:05.467
Now what?

23:21.066 --> 23:22.984
DAD

23:41.503 --> 23:43.463
DAD

23:46.424 --> 23:47.425
Hello?

23:48.009 --> 23:49.136
Hi, Na-hyun.

23:49.219 --> 23:51.638
You're busy, right? Let me make it quick.

23:51.721 --> 23:55.100
Your birthday is coming next week,

23:55.934 --> 24:01.148
so your mom wants to make you
a homemade birthday meal.

24:01.231 --> 24:02.232
Can you come over?

24:02.816 --> 24:04.234
That'd be too much of a hassle.

24:04.317 --> 24:05.485
Let's just dine outside.

24:06.069 --> 24:08.113
Oh, should we?

24:08.655 --> 24:10.365
S-Sure, why not?

24:10.448 --> 24:13.285
Let's dine out
and celebrate the happy day.

24:13.368 --> 24:16.538
How about Japanese food?
It's your favorite. I'll book a table.

24:17.122 --> 24:18.039
Okay.

24:19.624 --> 24:20.959
Thanks, Dad.

24:21.042 --> 24:23.587
<i>No problem. Bye.</i>

24:33.388 --> 24:34.306
Hello?

24:34.389 --> 24:36.183
<i>Is this Attorney Han Na-hyun?</i>

24:36.725 --> 24:39.686
<i>Word says you're an outstanding attorney.</i>

24:39.769 --> 24:42.105
<i>Will you be able to help me?</i>

24:42.647 --> 24:43.732
Yes, of course.

24:43.815 --> 24:46.610
Please text me your address.
I'll visit you right away.

24:48.069 --> 24:49.029
All right.

24:49.946 --> 24:52.073
I gave you a special cut.

24:53.366 --> 24:54.659
Thank you as always.

24:57.329 --> 24:59.164
No news about ghosts yet?

24:59.873 --> 25:00.832
No.

25:00.916 --> 25:02.042
Are you disappointed?

25:02.667 --> 25:03.501
Excuse me?

25:03.585 --> 25:06.796
I've read the faces of followers
for over 20 years.

25:07.631 --> 25:11.384
I can easily tell if one is happy,
sad, relieved, or disappointed.

25:12.761 --> 25:14.554
You're as sharp as a needle.

25:14.638 --> 25:16.264
Is I-rang aware?

25:16.848 --> 25:17.682
Of what?

25:17.766 --> 25:22.479
That you visited the shaman
at Unit 501 of the Okcheon Building.

25:22.562 --> 25:25.482
He doesn't know and it must stay that way.

25:29.361 --> 25:31.238
-Take responsibility!
-Take responsibility!

25:31.321 --> 25:33.323
Take responsibility!

25:33.406 --> 25:36.034
Punish the scammers!

25:36.117 --> 25:38.578
-Punish them!
-Punish them!

25:38.662 --> 25:42.374
-Where did our money go?
-Compensate the victims!

25:42.457 --> 25:45.043
-Compensate!
-Compensate!

25:45.126 --> 25:47.462
Make amends!

25:47.545 --> 25:49.839
-Make amends!
-Make amends!

25:49.923 --> 25:52.425
Take responsibility and make amends!

25:52.509 --> 25:53.551
Take responsibility!

25:53.635 --> 25:56.304
-Take responsibility!
-Take responsibility!

25:57.055 --> 25:58.807
I'm just as troubled, you know.

25:59.724 --> 26:01.893
Everyone can be happy
if we just build the apartment.

26:02.519 --> 26:05.689
But the landowner is insisting
on not selling the land.

26:05.772 --> 26:08.566
There's really nothing I can do.

26:08.650 --> 26:13.238
Didn't you advertise
as if the land had already been purchased?

26:13.822 --> 26:15.240
No, not at all.

26:16.074 --> 26:18.493
Oh, you'll know
if you take a look at the contract.

26:29.045 --> 26:30.422
TERMINATION OF THE CONTRACT

26:30.505 --> 26:32.424
The terms here are difficult.

26:32.966 --> 26:34.134
The sentences are complex too.

26:35.218 --> 26:38.096
It's incomprehensible even for me.

26:38.179 --> 26:40.015
That's what a contract is for.

26:40.640 --> 26:45.437
You just have to prove my innocence
with this ambiguous contract.

26:48.440 --> 26:49.357
Can you do it?

26:59.409 --> 27:00.243
Hi, Mr. Bae.

27:00.327 --> 27:01.911
<i>I-rang, where are you right now?</i>

27:01.995 --> 27:04.331
Me? I'm at my sister's restaurant.
Why do you ask?

27:05.540 --> 27:06.750
Thank goodness.

27:06.833 --> 27:09.002
You haven't visited
Seongmyeong Construction yet, right?

27:09.085 --> 27:10.503
Do not go whatsoever.

27:11.254 --> 27:12.172
What?

27:12.255 --> 27:13.840
I'm sorry, I-rang.

27:14.341 --> 27:18.928
The client I set you up with
turns out to involve a construction gang.

27:19.637 --> 27:21.723
What? A construction gang?

27:23.892 --> 27:27.020
Hello, I'm calling
because Attorney Bae Il-do referred me--

27:29.022 --> 27:31.775
He already gave you a call.

27:32.817 --> 27:34.944
I'm calling

27:35.653 --> 27:39.491
to recommend you
an outstanding attorney I know.

27:40.408 --> 27:41.368
Shoot.

27:42.035 --> 27:43.328
Mr. Bae, text me the address.

27:43.912 --> 27:44.746
What?

27:44.829 --> 27:46.498
Text me the address now!

27:49.334 --> 27:51.628
Attorney Han went office-hunting

27:51.711 --> 27:53.797
and handed out her business cards
at the courthouse.

27:54.464 --> 27:56.174
It seems she'll open her own practice.

28:00.178 --> 28:02.847
And this morning,
she took on her first case.

28:04.307 --> 28:06.267
Her client is Seongmyeong Construction,

28:06.351 --> 28:08.436
a shady company that runs
a pre-sale fraud scheme.

28:08.520 --> 28:09.687
ATTORNEY HAN'S POTENTIAL CASE

28:09.771 --> 28:13.483
After all that big talk,
this is the case she takes on?

28:14.692 --> 28:15.944
Good going.

28:16.528 --> 28:18.655
It seems dangerous. What should we do?

28:19.781 --> 28:20.949
Nothing.

28:21.658 --> 28:25.078
I'll take this chance
to watch her high ego snap.

28:26.454 --> 28:27.414
It's going to be fun.

28:31.459 --> 28:32.627
Wait.

28:33.753 --> 28:37.507
Just keep tabs on her in secret.

28:38.341 --> 28:39.217
Yes, sir.

28:46.015 --> 28:48.059
What's taking you so long to answer?

28:55.400 --> 28:56.818
I can't do it.

29:01.364 --> 29:03.241
What? You can't?

29:07.704 --> 29:10.039
You must be mistaken.

29:10.707 --> 29:12.584
I'm saying I can't do it
with this much info.

29:13.209 --> 29:14.711
What does that mean?

29:14.794 --> 29:16.629
You're so lucky, sir.

29:17.172 --> 29:20.842
I'm very experienced
in pre-construction sales cases.

29:21.426 --> 29:23.178
Especially, this kind of scam…

29:23.261 --> 29:27.640
I mean, business is my expertise
because I'm so used to it.

29:29.392 --> 29:30.393
So?

29:31.478 --> 29:34.022
The essential condition of winning a case
is information.

29:34.606 --> 29:38.568
The more information you have,
the more backup plans you can have.

29:38.651 --> 29:42.989
For example, a fabricated document
of the land purchase.

29:43.072 --> 29:47.118
Or an agreement you got
through blackmailing allottees.

29:47.911 --> 29:49.412
I need all kinds of materials.

29:49.496 --> 29:52.332
There's no such thing.
We do everything by the law.

29:52.999 --> 29:55.710
Sir, you shouldn't
underestimate the prosecution.

29:56.377 --> 29:59.047
One search and seizure is enough
to find everything like dominoes.

29:59.130 --> 30:01.925
Once they start tearing you apart,
you're finished.

30:02.717 --> 30:06.012
Your attorney has to
fight the prosecution for you.

30:06.095 --> 30:09.140
Of course, I need to know everything.

30:13.978 --> 30:17.607
If you get raided,
it'll all go down the drain, I tell you.

30:17.690 --> 30:21.027
You'll be sentenced
to at least five years in jail. Too bad.

30:38.044 --> 30:39.587
Good thinking.

30:42.632 --> 30:43.591
Where's the bathroom?

30:43.675 --> 30:45.677
It's at the end of the hallway outside.

30:48.847 --> 30:50.056
Oh!

30:50.682 --> 30:52.684
A glass of iced Americano, please.

30:52.767 --> 30:53.852
I'm a bit thirsty.

30:53.935 --> 30:55.562
The hell are you saying?

30:55.645 --> 30:57.021
What are you waiting for?

30:57.605 --> 30:59.858
She wants an iced Americano.

31:29.762 --> 31:30.597
Prosecutor Kim?

31:30.680 --> 31:33.266
Hi, Na-hyun. Are you sick?
What happened to your voice?

31:33.933 --> 31:35.768
I'm well, and I have a favor to ask.

31:36.603 --> 31:40.565
Do you know Seongmyeong Construction?
It's under investigation lately.

31:41.149 --> 31:42.901
Yes, it's a vicious pre-sale scammer.

31:42.984 --> 31:44.986
We don't have enough evidence
to indict them.

31:45.069 --> 31:46.696
I'll get you that evidence.

31:46.779 --> 31:48.531
Come straight to the address I text you.

31:49.157 --> 31:52.452
Send the nearby police first
since there's no time, okay?

31:56.122 --> 31:59.709
SEONGMYEONG CONSTRUCTION

31:59.792 --> 32:02.754
Apologies. I drank a lot yesterday.

32:38.998 --> 32:40.333
This should be enough

32:40.959 --> 32:42.502
to make you rot for at least ten years.

32:43.294 --> 32:46.130
-Rot?
-In prison, of course.

32:46.214 --> 32:47.382
What?

32:47.465 --> 32:51.094
You preyed on people's lifelong dreams
of owning a home.

32:51.177 --> 32:52.387
That deserves punishment.

32:53.846 --> 32:56.641
But sir, you're really lucky

32:57.308 --> 32:59.185
because I'm going to give you a chance.

33:00.061 --> 33:03.606
Turn yourself in
and give the money back to the victims.

33:03.690 --> 33:04.774
Are you out of your mind?

33:05.858 --> 33:07.819
You've got some nerve, don't you?

33:07.902 --> 33:09.696
Why don't I mince you to pieces?

33:13.324 --> 33:14.200
What's that noise?

33:14.993 --> 33:15.994
Oh, dear.

33:16.661 --> 33:18.371
The police are already here.

33:20.206 --> 33:22.542
You should've reflected
on yourself sooner.

33:22.625 --> 33:24.043
You crazy bitch.

33:24.752 --> 33:25.837
Attorney Han!

33:27.422 --> 33:29.966
You little punks!

33:30.800 --> 33:32.427
How did you know I was here?

33:32.510 --> 33:33.720
Are you okay?

33:34.345 --> 33:36.472
What about the police? Where are they?

33:36.556 --> 33:39.100
T-The police? What police?

33:40.018 --> 33:41.310
What's with you people?

33:42.770 --> 33:43.938
How fast can you run 100 m?

33:44.814 --> 33:45.982
Fifteen seconds.

33:46.816 --> 33:47.900
Run.

33:48.609 --> 33:49.694
Hurry!

33:49.777 --> 33:50.737
Get them!

33:53.322 --> 33:54.824
Stop right there!

33:57.201 --> 33:58.745
You bastard, stop!

34:12.633 --> 34:14.010
Where did they go? Boys!

34:14.093 --> 34:16.387
Go this way! And you guys, go that way!

34:31.152 --> 34:32.445
I'm sorry.

34:33.279 --> 34:35.865
Don't talk to me. I'm out of breath.

34:36.491 --> 34:39.202
I didn't know they were dangerous people.

34:40.369 --> 34:42.288
You gave him my number?

34:42.872 --> 34:46.334
You got fired because of me.
I had to do something.

34:46.417 --> 34:49.462
Why did you come alone, though?
You should've come with the police.

34:50.046 --> 34:51.047
You're right.

34:51.631 --> 34:55.343
I rushed here in case you got hurt.

34:56.511 --> 34:57.762
Are you hurt at all?

34:59.097 --> 35:00.348
Are you worried about me?

35:01.057 --> 35:02.308
Of course.

35:03.726 --> 35:05.853
There they are! Over there!

35:06.395 --> 35:08.106
Hurry up! They're over there.

35:08.189 --> 35:09.607
Run! Hurry up.

35:09.690 --> 35:11.526
-Hey!
-Stop right there!

35:23.329 --> 35:24.705
Damn it, boys!

35:24.789 --> 35:26.833
-Get in there!
-Open up!

35:27.667 --> 35:30.586
-You bastard!
-Unlock this door now!

35:37.093 --> 35:38.594
-This is not good at all.
-Hey!

35:40.930 --> 35:43.891
Give me back the documents,
and I'll let you go peacefully.

35:43.975 --> 35:45.893
-Open the doors!
-Documents?

35:46.978 --> 35:48.479
What are those?

35:49.063 --> 35:51.149
Evidence to put them in jail.

35:51.899 --> 35:53.776
You mean, evidence to get us killed?

35:54.819 --> 35:56.487
We're not going to die.

35:56.571 --> 35:58.239
We'll turn this crisis
into an opportunity.

35:58.781 --> 36:01.367
What makes you that confident?

36:10.960 --> 36:12.378
What now?

36:17.508 --> 36:19.135
-I have a good idea.
-What?

36:22.013 --> 36:25.141
Don't you come close,
or I'll scatter these to the victims.

36:25.224 --> 36:27.226
-Wait.
-No.

36:27.977 --> 36:30.188
What? Are you scared?

36:30.271 --> 36:32.106
Are you scared? Are you?

36:32.190 --> 36:33.316
Is that it?

36:40.531 --> 36:42.867
-Damn.
-She startled us all.

36:42.950 --> 36:44.118
I knew something was off.

36:47.288 --> 36:48.539
Attorney Shin.

36:48.623 --> 36:49.457
What now?

36:50.082 --> 36:51.459
You're good at fighting, right?

36:52.168 --> 36:53.252
What?

36:55.171 --> 36:56.547
Kill them.

36:56.631 --> 36:59.091
-Geez.
-Hey, come over here.

36:59.175 --> 37:00.301
Come here.

37:05.139 --> 37:06.641
Bring it on!

37:20.571 --> 37:22.031
Hey.

37:22.114 --> 37:23.115
Let go of her!

37:37.505 --> 37:39.840
Move! Out of the way.

37:40.424 --> 37:41.425
Attorney Shin!

37:42.969 --> 37:44.387
Freeze and get down!

37:44.929 --> 37:46.639
-Arrest them.
-Yes, sir.

37:47.223 --> 37:48.140
Get down.

37:49.308 --> 37:51.352
-Hands above your heads.
-Stand up now.

37:51.936 --> 37:53.354
-Stand up.
-I hear you, okay?

37:54.772 --> 37:57.733
You too. Stand up. Come along.

37:58.276 --> 37:59.568
Walk faster. Move.

38:00.611 --> 38:01.487
Attorney Shin.

38:02.738 --> 38:03.572
Are you okay?

38:04.365 --> 38:05.408
Pull yourself together.

38:08.494 --> 38:10.746
I'm… okay.

38:11.330 --> 38:12.873
You're not okay.

38:14.166 --> 38:16.460
You shouldn't have come here alone!

38:21.590 --> 38:22.675
Are you hurt?

38:26.971 --> 38:27.805
TAEBAEK

38:27.888 --> 38:29.807
So what happened?

38:29.890 --> 38:31.684
Even the prosecution swooped in.

38:31.767 --> 38:33.185
All the related scammers were arrested.

38:33.269 --> 38:35.104
Not that, I'm talking about Han Na-hyun.

38:36.522 --> 38:37.732
Is Attorney Han okay?

38:38.899 --> 38:41.277
She almost got hurt,

38:41.360 --> 38:42.945
but Shin I-rang rescued her.

38:45.197 --> 38:47.575
Shin I-rang? What did he do?

38:47.658 --> 38:48.909
Well…

38:49.785 --> 38:54.665
The gang surrounded Attorney Han
and things were about to get physical

38:54.749 --> 38:56.375
when Shin I-rang threw himself--

38:56.459 --> 38:57.710
That's enough.

38:57.793 --> 38:58.627
You're dismissed.

38:58.711 --> 39:01.297
That guy isn't particularly
a strong fighter,

39:01.380 --> 39:04.008
but he tried his best
to protect Attorney Han…

39:05.384 --> 39:06.594
Go back to work, I said.

39:07.261 --> 39:08.179
Yes, sir.

39:24.904 --> 39:27.114
OKCHEON BUILDING

39:38.376 --> 39:42.254
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

39:53.057 --> 39:54.392
Attorney Han?

39:55.643 --> 39:57.478
What are you doing here?

39:58.270 --> 39:59.980
I went to your office
and you weren't there.

40:00.731 --> 40:02.858
Apparently, everyone in the neighborhood
knows you.

40:02.942 --> 40:05.069
I've lived here for a long time.

40:06.153 --> 40:07.238
I see.

40:08.406 --> 40:10.783
So what brings you here?

40:16.747 --> 40:18.541
I forgot that I had plans.

40:19.041 --> 40:19.875
Plans?

40:19.959 --> 40:22.753
I'm supposed to meet Je-hun at the
playground. He's from Class Flower Petal.

40:24.004 --> 40:24.839
Out of the blue?

40:27.675 --> 40:28.509
Good luck!

40:30.511 --> 40:31.762
What?

40:31.846 --> 40:33.264
Da-bong!

40:51.740 --> 40:53.868
Is it okay to drink?
You have an injured arm.

40:55.244 --> 40:56.996
I'll just have sips.

41:14.346 --> 41:17.516
Shouldn't you go home early?
Your daughter must be waiting.

41:18.684 --> 41:19.685
My daughter?

41:21.145 --> 41:23.355
Oh, you mean Da-bong?

41:23.898 --> 41:24.732
She's my niece.

41:25.524 --> 41:28.527
My dear beloved niece.

41:29.570 --> 41:30.863
Doesn't she look a lot like me?

41:31.906 --> 41:33.115
As if.

41:34.158 --> 41:36.911
She looked cute, keen, and smart.

41:38.579 --> 41:39.497
You think?

42:08.817 --> 42:11.612
I saw you hand out your business cards.
Didn't you get any clients?

42:12.196 --> 42:14.573
No. Not even one.

42:15.366 --> 42:17.576
Work for other clients, then.

42:18.577 --> 42:20.496
Those special clients…

42:21.997 --> 42:23.374
who are visible only to you.

42:26.168 --> 42:27.545
I don't have such clients.

42:28.587 --> 42:29.547
How unusual.

42:30.673 --> 42:33.926
You said you could see ghosts
like it was a bad habit.

42:35.177 --> 42:36.178
I can't

42:37.263 --> 42:38.514
see them anymore.

42:40.933 --> 42:41.976
I see.

42:44.562 --> 42:46.855
Anyway, why did you come to see me?

42:59.702 --> 43:01.078
To apologize.

43:01.161 --> 43:02.371
Apologize?

43:04.915 --> 43:06.125
Oh.

43:07.001 --> 43:09.670
I'm the one who sent you there.

43:10.254 --> 43:11.463
I owe you an apology.

43:11.547 --> 43:12.923
Not for your injury.

43:14.550 --> 43:18.053
I had job interviews
after resigning from Taebaek.

43:18.637 --> 43:21.265
I saw a red X mark on my name.

43:23.475 --> 43:26.812
When I saw it, it really offended me.

43:29.023 --> 43:30.524
It sure was shitty

43:31.609 --> 43:33.611
going through it myself.

43:38.490 --> 43:39.867
Let me apologize.

43:41.035 --> 43:42.953
I'm truly sorry. I mean it.

43:45.664 --> 43:48.292
That's okay. It's all in the past now.

43:49.501 --> 43:50.419
No.

43:51.503 --> 43:54.673
You should never have
been mistreated like that.

43:56.383 --> 43:58.177
You're not at fault.

44:08.937 --> 44:10.230
I'm sorry.

44:12.024 --> 44:14.234
I wasn't meaning
to talk about your father.

44:14.318 --> 44:15.903
It's partly my fault.

44:17.863 --> 44:20.115
I knew my dad was a corrupt prosecutor,

44:21.450 --> 44:24.078
but I insisted on becoming an attorney.

44:25.537 --> 44:27.081
Don't say that.

44:28.415 --> 44:30.793
It's all right. That's the truth.

44:32.169 --> 44:33.420
I actually did wonder

44:35.005 --> 44:39.218
why you chose the same kind of job
as your father's

44:40.594 --> 44:43.347
instead of an ordinary job.

44:47.935 --> 44:49.269
Perhaps,

44:51.230 --> 44:53.690
I believed in my dad

44:54.608 --> 44:55.692
all along.

44:56.318 --> 44:57.319
<i>Dad!</i>

44:57.403 --> 44:58.946
I-rang.

45:01.365 --> 45:02.574
Did you wait long?

45:04.326 --> 45:05.494
Did the trial take long?

45:05.577 --> 45:11.208
It took me quite some time to bring those
who harassed good people to justice.

45:11.291 --> 45:13.085
I want to be like you when I grow up.

45:14.837 --> 45:16.046
Will you?

45:16.130 --> 45:17.172
Sure thing.

45:18.549 --> 45:21.301
-You'll get to work in there later.
<i>-Or maybe</i>

45:21.385 --> 45:23.429
<i>I wanted to believe in him.</i>

45:34.022 --> 45:36.024
I knew I shouldn't have taken this path

45:37.818 --> 45:39.903
but I couldn't give up…

45:41.864 --> 45:43.240
like a fool.

45:50.706 --> 45:53.000
I'm not sure how you'll take this…

45:59.381 --> 46:01.008
but I understand you.

46:08.640 --> 46:09.850
It was actually

46:11.602 --> 46:13.520
my older sister's dream to be an attorney.

46:14.980 --> 46:17.107
It's going to be real fun.
I'm telling you!

46:17.191 --> 46:18.317
We gotta hurry there.

46:18.400 --> 46:20.777
Okay, we're already on our way.

46:21.361 --> 46:22.571
The light turned green.

46:23.447 --> 46:26.533
-Slow down.
-What are you waiting for? Come on.

46:32.498 --> 46:33.665
Na-hyun!

46:48.597 --> 46:49.431
So-hyun.

46:51.308 --> 46:52.351
So-hyun!

46:57.564 --> 47:00.609
No… So-hyun!

47:00.692 --> 47:01.860
So-hyun!

47:05.614 --> 47:07.616
I MUST WIN EVERY TIME!

47:08.575 --> 47:10.077
HAN SO-HYUN
LAW AND POLITICS

47:17.584 --> 47:19.419
<i>After my sister died in an accident,</i>

47:20.420 --> 47:23.465
<i>I decided to become an attorney.</i>

47:25.509 --> 47:27.177
She died because of me.

47:29.513 --> 47:32.849
I shouldn't be chasing a dream of my own.

47:39.898 --> 47:43.652
So since then,
I've been living the life of my sister.

47:52.035 --> 47:53.745
That must be why

47:55.163 --> 47:57.791
you didn't know when to stop.

47:58.417 --> 48:00.002
Did I not?

48:01.336 --> 48:03.088
I can't be so sure,

48:04.881 --> 48:06.174
but your sister

48:07.426 --> 48:10.178
was probably proud of you.

48:11.888 --> 48:14.224
You're always diligent

48:14.766 --> 48:16.184
and precise.

48:16.768 --> 48:19.688
And you're so…

48:19.771 --> 48:21.189
down to earth.

48:24.943 --> 48:26.695
Not really.

48:29.406 --> 48:30.574
But thanks.

48:32.868 --> 48:36.163
I kind of get the reasons
behind how you've behaved too.

48:37.456 --> 48:38.915
You…

48:39.541 --> 48:43.712
wanted to be like your dad,
who was your childhood hero, didn't you?

48:48.175 --> 48:50.135
I think you're on the right track.

48:58.685 --> 48:59.978
I must say,

49:01.938 --> 49:04.524
you also have a great way
of interpreting things.

49:06.068 --> 49:08.820
Anyway, thanks.

49:20.874 --> 49:21.792
Careful.

49:24.336 --> 49:25.337
Be careful.

49:38.892 --> 49:42.312
The guy from the chauffeur service
will be here soon, so wait a bit.

49:44.439 --> 49:46.316
-Did you call for a driver?
-Yes.

49:46.400 --> 49:47.359
Right here, sir.

50:04.710 --> 50:06.920
-Could I play some music?
-Sure.

50:48.211 --> 50:49.421
THE LATE HAN SO-HYUN

50:49.504 --> 50:51.965
WE LOVE OUR BRIGHT
AND RIGHTEOUS SO-HYUN

51:09.149 --> 51:10.233
NAME: SHIN I-RANG

51:35.967 --> 51:37.677
<i>She died because of me.</i>

51:38.804 --> 51:42.015
<i>I shouldn't be chasing a dream of my own.</i>

52:01.701 --> 52:03.829
Attorney Han, we're here.

52:18.677 --> 52:19.636
Let me.

52:28.937 --> 52:30.146
Wait.

52:33.692 --> 52:37.362
Attorney Han, we're at your house now.

52:38.738 --> 52:40.866
Your shoes. Take off your shoes.

52:49.666 --> 52:50.667
Careful.

52:58.133 --> 53:01.303
Attorney Han, wake up.

53:47.557 --> 53:48.558
Attorney Han.

53:49.601 --> 53:52.938
If you wake up in the middle of the night,
make sure you go to your room.

53:58.985 --> 53:59.903
And…

54:02.781 --> 54:04.532
I'm truly sorry

54:06.034 --> 54:07.410
that my ghost-seeing ability…

54:12.958 --> 54:14.334
put you through so much.

54:20.173 --> 54:22.842
I'll go now.

54:31.476 --> 54:32.978
It's a shame…

54:35.146 --> 54:36.481
you can't see…

54:39.609 --> 54:40.652
I wish I could see…

54:45.240 --> 54:46.616
my sister.

55:20.483 --> 55:22.360
SO-HYUN AND NA-HYUN
ON JUNE 8, 1999

55:24.821 --> 55:28.575
HAN SO-HYUN'S 19TH BIRTHDAY
ON JULY 7, 2012

56:37.560 --> 56:40.480
I-rang, what are you doing here
instead of sleeping?

56:41.189 --> 56:43.608
Nothing. I'm just sitting here.

57:00.708 --> 57:02.043
You aren't just sitting here.

57:02.585 --> 57:04.003
Something's going on.

57:06.631 --> 57:09.926
What's troubling you?
You were excited about not seeing ghosts.

57:10.718 --> 57:11.594
Bong-su.

57:13.429 --> 57:14.430
The truth is,

57:15.431 --> 57:18.184
I know how to see ghosts.

57:19.519 --> 57:21.521
-What?
-But…

57:23.148 --> 57:24.816
I was trying to not see them.

57:27.986 --> 57:30.947
I know helping ghosts is a good deed,

57:32.490 --> 57:35.201
but I couldn't ignore
my family's concerns.

57:36.411 --> 57:38.830
And it was nice to be back

57:40.415 --> 57:42.208
to my ordinary everyday life.

57:46.963 --> 57:48.548
I also thought it was right

57:50.133 --> 57:53.052
to let bygones be bygones.

57:56.181 --> 57:57.390
But then,

57:59.976 --> 58:01.728
I realized something.

58:04.272 --> 58:05.648
It's a shame…

58:07.775 --> 58:09.068
you can't see…

58:10.904 --> 58:12.697
<i>I failed to understand</i>

58:13.865 --> 58:15.158
the desperate longing

58:16.409 --> 58:18.578
to see a beloved one

58:20.872 --> 58:22.790
one last time.

58:26.794 --> 58:28.129
<i>To them,</i>

58:28.963 --> 58:30.924
<i>it's never over for them.</i>

58:31.966 --> 58:34.511
<i>It can never be bygones for them.</i>

58:34.594 --> 58:35.553
I love you.

58:35.637 --> 58:38.681
I love you, Dad.

58:39.307 --> 58:41.184
But I simply thought it was all over

58:42.310 --> 58:44.854
and it was meant to be let go.

58:50.944 --> 58:55.823
I thought you were finally
starting to breathe again,

58:57.450 --> 58:58.618
but I see you've got

58:59.827 --> 59:01.496
a lot on your mind.

59:07.794 --> 59:08.795
So,

59:10.547 --> 59:12.215
what do you want to do?

59:20.139 --> 59:21.933
If this is my destiny,

59:24.018 --> 59:24.894
I will…

59:27.188 --> 59:28.189
accept that destiny.

59:45.582 --> 59:47.584
SEOUL

59:47.667 --> 59:49.419
Thank you, sir.

59:49.502 --> 59:51.629
-Have a good night.
-Bye.

01:00:02.223 --> 01:00:05.727
OKCHEON BUILDING

01:01:02.033 --> 01:01:03.701
I'm ready.

01:01:07.246 --> 01:01:08.873
My doors are open for anyone now.

01:01:44.409 --> 01:01:47.995
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

01:01:52.291 --> 01:01:54.293
SEOUL

01:02:17.316 --> 01:02:19.819
NA-HYUN'S MOM

01:02:20.445 --> 01:02:21.446
Hi, honey.

01:02:21.529 --> 01:02:23.948
Honey, did you have dinner?

01:02:24.031 --> 01:02:25.366
What time are you coming home today?

01:02:25.450 --> 01:02:27.368
I'm just about to head home now.

01:02:27.994 --> 01:02:29.912
I feel a little down today.

01:02:29.996 --> 01:02:31.956
Why? Did something happen?

01:02:32.540 --> 01:02:33.875
Do you remember

01:02:34.709 --> 01:02:38.588
when we went to Seocho-dong
after what happened to So-hyun?

01:02:41.174 --> 01:02:42.717
Of course, I remember.

01:02:43.468 --> 01:02:44.969
There's no way I can forget it.

01:02:45.553 --> 01:02:47.722
I'm in front of that building right now.

01:02:49.474 --> 01:02:51.058
The shaman's house is gone.

01:02:52.185 --> 01:02:54.353
It's a law office now.

01:02:58.524 --> 01:03:02.528
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

01:03:16.083 --> 01:03:16.918
Wow.

01:03:17.960 --> 01:03:19.295
The stars are beautiful.

01:03:26.719 --> 01:03:27.887
They really came.

01:03:42.735 --> 01:03:44.946
Excuse me. Are you…

01:03:57.750 --> 01:03:59.752
HAN SO-HYUN'S 19TH BIRTHDAY
ON JULY 7, 2012

01:04:41.168 --> 01:04:42.211
<i>That's enough!</i>

01:04:42.295 --> 01:04:43.629
<i>If you're drunk, keep on walking.</i>

01:04:43.713 --> 01:04:45.506
How could you use violence
against students?

01:04:45.590 --> 01:04:48.050
Three boys were ganging up on one kid.

01:04:48.134 --> 01:04:50.678
<i>That bastard who beat you up</i>
<i>got an attorney.</i>

01:04:50.761 --> 01:04:53.180
<i>It'll take no time for her</i>
<i>to find out what you've done.</i>

01:04:53.264 --> 01:04:54.599
<i>-Stop.</i>
<i>-I'm going to kill him.</i>

01:04:54.682 --> 01:04:57.894
He's a diligent kid that will be happy
if he can just get over this hump.

01:04:57.977 --> 01:04:59.979
<i>-I'm going to do something about it.</i>
<i>-I'll kill you for real.</i>

01:05:00.062 --> 01:05:01.314
<i>Why would I die?</i>

01:05:01.397 --> 01:05:02.565
<i>It's your turn to die.</i>

01:05:04.775 --> 01:05:06.068
<i>Jun-ho!</i>

01:05:07.403 --> 01:05:12.241
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
